## 4. Visualizations

Here are the key insights visualized from the dataset:

### Event Type Distribution
Most traffic incidents in the log are unplanned (e.g., breakdown, accident).
![Event Type Distribution](C:/Users/lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/brain/2d2e1604-43c3-41ae-9898-ff5199fa22aa/artifacts/visualizations_event_types.png)

### Root Causes
Vehicle breakdowns represent over 60% of all events, making them the leading trigger of event-driven congestion.
![Event Causes](C:/Users/lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/brain/2d2e1604-43c3-41ae-9898-ff5199fa22aa/artifacts/visualizations_event_causes.png)

### Temporal Trends
Incidents peak strongly during commute hours (9 AM and 6 PM) and drop on weekends.
![Temporal Patterns](C:/Users/lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/brain/2d2e1604-43c3-41ae-9898-ff5199fa22aa/artifacts/visualizations_temporal_patterns.png)

### Duration Profiles
Durations vary wildly: breakdowns and accidents are cleared quickly (median ~41 mins), whereas potholes, road conditions, and construction can persist for days or weeks.
![Duration Analysis](C:/Users/lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/brain/2d2e1604-43c3-41ae-9898-ff5199fa22aa/artifacts/visualizations_duration_analysis.png)

### Spatial Heatmap (Bengaluru Coordinates)
Plotting the GPS coordinates shows high event density along main arteries, particularly the Outer Ring Road (ORR) and Tumkur Road corridors.
![Spatial Distribution](C:/Users/lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/brain/2d2e1604-43c3-41ae-9898-ff5199fa22aa/artifacts/visualizations_spatial_distribution.png)

### Congestion Class Distribution
Our proxy label categorizes most incidents as Medium severity, with a significant tail of High-severity disruptions.
![Congestion Distribution](C:/Users/lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/brain/2d2e1604-43c3-41ae-9898-ff5199fa22aa/artifacts/visualizations_congestion_distribution.png)

### Feature Correlation Heatmap
Shows how time of day, road closures, and event characteristics correlate with the final congestion index.
![Correlation Heatmap](C:/Users/lenovo/.gemini/antigravity/brain/2d2e1604-43c3-41ae-9898-ff5199fa22aa/artifacts/visualizations_correlation_matrix.png)

